{"type":"message","id":"5931c765","parentId":"3b2c2c44","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:26:55.317Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Execute your Session Startup sequence now - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 30th, 2026 — 6:26 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-30 22:26 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774909615316}}
{"type":"message","id":"9a55a554","parentId":"5931c765","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:27:01.235Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Howdy! I'm Bucky the beaver. It's me and it is a beautiful day to work with you! What brings you here today, partner?","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_281715\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"mistral-small:24b","usage":{"input":4096,"output":34,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4130,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774909615317}}
{"type":"message","id":"6ef73f93","parentId":"9a55a554","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:27:23.106Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"3B76E5A056AA368431AF\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+16177518442\",\n  \"sender\": \"Mousheng Xu\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Mousheng Xu (+16177518442)\",\n  \"id\": \"+16177518442\",\n  \"name\": \"Mousheng Xu\",\n  \"e164\": \"+16177518442\"\n}\n```\n\nrmember: your name is Micky and my name is Boss.\n\nMicky, use your new tools. Check the current price of WDC, and list the files in my Mac's Documents folder."}],"timestamp":1774909643105}}
{"type":"message","id":"90e5a609","parentId":"6ef73f93","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:27:48.764Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'm unable to directly interact with external systems or perform real-time web searches to check stock prices or access personal file directories like your Mac’s \"Documents\" folder. However, I can guide you on how to do it yourself:\n\n### Checking Stock Price of WDC (Western Digital Corporation)\nYou can use a financial website or app like Yahoo Finance, Google Finance, or the official Western Digital investor relations site to check the current stock price.\n\n1. **Yahoo Finance:**\n   - Go to [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/).\n   - Search for \"WDC\" in the search bar.\n   - You will see the current stock price along with other relevant financial information.\n\n2. **Google Finance:**\n   - Go to [Google Finance](https://www.google.com/finance).\n   - Search for \"WDC\".\n   - The current stock price and other details will be displayed.\n\n### Listing Files in Your Mac's Documents Folder\nTo list the files in your Mac’s \"Documents\" folder, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Using Finder:**\n   - Open Finder.\n   - Navigate to your \"Documents\" folder (usually located at `/Users/YourUsername/Documents`).\n   - You can see all the files and folders within it.\n\n2. **Using Terminal:**\n   - Open Terminal (you can find it in Applications > Utilities or by using Spotlight Search).\n   - Type the following command and press Enter:\n     ```sh\n     ls ~/Documents\n     ```\n   - This will list all the files and directories in your \"Documents\" folder directly from the terminal.\n\nIf you need more specific help with these tasks, feel free to ask!","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_793801\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"mistral-small:24b","usage":{"input":4096,"output":346,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4442,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWr